strong.font:
April, 22, 2020
Boulder Elementary School Community,
The Governor of Montana issued an order today keeping Montana's schools closed for onsite learning through May 7th. We will continue with remote learning through May 7th. The Boulder Elementary School Board of Trustees will be meeting soon to determine further action on this order. The Boulder Elementary School Board of Trustees will take every step to ensure the safety of our students, families and staff. The district office will keep you updated on any future action regarding school closures.
Regards,
Ms. Pace
​

font.strong: Meal Delivery is being made Monday's Wednesday's and Friday's directly to homes between noon and 2pm. With the exception of the week of April 13th when deliveries will be made Tues. and Thurs. Children will still receive all meals for the week. Meals include Breakfast, Lunch and a snack for the day,
font.br:
Meals are available to any person 18 and under regardless of free and reduced status or being enrolled in school.
please email sarina.eckman@bgs.k12.mt.us for more information or to be included in meal count.

br.font:
As we work together during this time, I want to express my gratitude to all of you for your hard work and flexibility. Next week is our Easter Break- April 9, 10, and the 13. Easter Break will allow students and parents to take a much needed break. At this time school will resume April 24th. The information from the Governor’s office has been given in 2 week increments, and if any new school closures are announced you will be notified by text, email, or phone. It is possible the governor will extend the school closure through the end of April.
Take care of yourself and family! Exercise, get some fresh air, and practice social distancing!! We miss you all so much!!
Ms. Pace
